{"name":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","type":"npc","img":"icons/svg/ghost.svg","flags":{},"token":{"name":"Anastazia the Sorrowful Spirit","img":"icons/svg/ghost.svg"},"system":{"npcType":"broken_one","oppositionLevel":7,"wounds":{"max":3,"current":3,"extra":0},"soma":{"max":0,"current":0},"xp":0,"background":"Anastazia is a restless spirit, bound to the memory of her granddaughter Iskra. She can no longer speak directly to the living, only through dreams, whispers, and visions.","descriptors":["I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of my granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow me to communicate with the living except through dreams, whispers, and visions."],"gifts":["Spirit: Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged by magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may resist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. The target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from Anastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely whispered phrase.","Loving Grandmother: Anastazia always follows Iskra and protects her from danger. Thanks to her strong will, she can interact with the material world by moving objects and manipulating the environment, even inflicting a Wound on a target. If a subject is likely to help save her granddaughter, Anastazia will simply fill their mind with memories of her."],"agenda":"Preventing further harm to Iskra and finding a way to save my granddaughter’s soul.","conditions":[],"notes":"Anastazia is incorporeal. The Storyteller may allow her to manifest for narrative effect."},"_id":"528824b1f2212985"}
{"name":"Red-Hood Iskra","type":"npc","flags":{"btActorType":"broken_one","btNpcSubtype":"main","btCustomOL":"5"},"img":"icons/svg/blood.svg","system":{"npcType":"broken_one","attributes":{"soma":{"max":0,"current":0},"wounds":{"max":4,"current":0,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}},"xp":0},"descriptors":["I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I hide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made with my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the last gift of my mother."],"agenda":"To unleash her animalistic fury on Elizaveta and anyone who defends her. Taking revenge on my mother has become an obsession for me.","gifts":["Wolf's Blood: Iskra is moved by animalistic fury that allows her to act twice in the course of an exchange.","The Senses of a Wolf: Iskra's sense of smell has become infallible. The little girl will always be able to identify someone if she knows their scent, ignoring all kinds of disguise and even magic."],"conditions":[],"notes":""},"_id":"5f842f9436482069"}
{"name":"Iskra the Young Wolf","type":"npc","npcType":"broken_one","system":{"attributes":{"soma":{"max":6,"current":6},"wounds":{"max":3,"current":0,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}},"xp":0},"background":"I was abandoned by my mother in a large forest and survived by joining a pack of werewolves. After a year of honing my predatory skills, I tracked down the woman I once called 'Mother' and sank my fangs into her throat. My pack was dismantled by a group of Hunters and the Order captured me. After another year of education and training, I finally found in the Order my new pack and made the Hunters my trusted hunting companions. I serve the Order with strength and dedication, happy to do everything the alpha Hunter asks of me.","equipment":"A red cape of fine workmanship embroidered with the coat of arms of the Order, a wolf mask carved in wood, a broken clay doll (a memento of one of my few happy memories of my mother), a fang from the leader of my old pack, and a rag doll depicting a well-dressed girl — a gift from my beloved grandmother.","descriptors":["When I am calm, I still look like a small and helpless child and, thanks to this, adults tend to underestimate me. I struggle to behave like a normal child, but I can’t keep my wolfish side leashed forever.","I perform my best when I’m cooperating with my hunting companions. I quickly learn the strengths and weaknesses of the pack. I follow every order of anyone I consider more important than me within the pack, without hesitation or remorse.","I am a wolf child and I defend myself with fangs and claws. My sense of smell is infallible. I’m young and I know little about the world, so I am easily intimidated when I face something I don’t know."],"gifts":["The Red Hood: You can spend 1 Soma to look exactly like a common child. Create a Descriptor that contains one of the words Pretty, Small, or Sweet. As long as you maintain your disguise, no adult will notice you or consider you a potential danger. Receive 2 Additional Successes to the first action you take when you decide to drop your disguise and reveal who you are.","Pack: When you coordinate and act with one or more of your teammates against a common threat, you both get 1 Additional Success for your Position Check. At the end of the Scene, if you have resolved a significant issue thanks to the collaboration with your companions, you recover 1 Soma.","Dark Ego - The Young Wolf: Unleash your feral side, ready to bite anyone who opposes your pack. If you get an Outcome with an Increment on a Position Check, you can spend the Increment to take an additional action immediately. You can also inflict 1 Wound on yourself to perform an additional action after your normal action. You can’t perform more than 3 actions per Exchange. You may spend 1 Soma to memorize the smell of a person you are interacting with. You will always recognize them and it will be easy for you to follow their tracks even after a long time."],"darkEgo":{"trigger":"Give free rein to your feral side or fulfill a task for your pack with your wolf skills.","gift":"Dark Ego - The Young Wolf"},"conditions":[],"notes":""},"_id":"7f69339a2ae8c5fc"}
